^B@2^*BLarry Cohen: ^*N|cp||at|In this article, we discuss what happens when the Opponents interfere after our side has opened 1@H or 1@S. 

We will start with their overcall. If you want to sound modern, you can refer to these auctions as "in comp." That is short, of course, for "in competition". And that means the opponents (darn it!) are in our auction again.|
