The top experts are implementing a treatment that is gaining in popularity. When a 1@H or 1@S opening is doubled, they are using a convention that has many different names; I call it BROMAD (more in a moment). After 1-MAJ (DOUBLE) :|
PG| ***** 20 ***** |


AT|

A raise to two of the major is very weak ' about 3-7 points in support and 3-card support.|
PG| ***** 21 ***** |


AT|

A bid (artificial) in the suit 1-under is a better raise'about 7 -10 points in support.|
PG| ***** 22 ***** |


AT|

So, After 1@H (Double) :
2@H=A lousy (preemptive-type) raise with 3 trumps [with 4, you'd bid 3@H]

2@D=A legitimate raise with 3 or maybe 4 trumps (7 to 10).|
