qx||HT|B|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*BLarry Cohen: ^*N|cp||cs|6|at|This expanded version is spelled out here:

After 1@S (X): {Similar schedule after 1H is doubled}

1NT = clubs. Could be just a club suit, or might be CK Q T 3 intending to later raise spades (while getting in the club Feature first'maybe to direct the opening lead, or to help partner evaluate his hand for competing in spades).

2@C=Diamonds. Again, could be just diamonds, or might be a spade raise with diamond cards.

2@D=Hearts. (Heart suit, or a spade raise with heart cards).

2@H=One-under ' so a good raise (7 -10)

2@S=Bad raise.

Again, my WARNING! Do not try this at home (unless you just love to toy around and get into trouble). To read about one of my most embarrassing moments (showing the dangers of BROMAD), click this |CP|1|AT|^*Hlarryco.com/BridgeArticles/ArticleDetails.aspx?articleID=77^*N|CP||AT| link. 

